post_text:
Good Morning,

Just a few friendly reminders as we move into our 3rd week of hybrid learning.

(1) Students being sent home for COVID like symptoms (fever, headache, shortness of breath, cough, sore throat, vomiting, diarrhea, and abdominal pain) will result in all members of the household being sent home for precautionary purposes. This would also include if you are calling a student off in the morning. These are the guidelines established by the Illinois Department of Public Health.

(2) Dismissal will continue to be at 1:05 daily until September 25th.

Thank you again for your continued understanding and patience.

post_text:
WACC students.
Bus will leave at 7:25am beginning 8/20/20. Temperature checks will begin prior to entering the bus at 7:15am. Masks must be worn at all times during the bus ride. Students will pick up their Chromebook upon return at approximately 10:25am. Students will be temperature checked upon their return to MHS campus. Students that are driving separately will be expected to arrive shortly after the bus has arrived and participate in the temperature check in procedure. In-person learners will report to their class in progress after receiving their Chromebook. Remote learners will be expected to return home. During the 1:05 dismissal schedule, the return from WACC will occur during the 4th period class. WACC students should make arrangements with their teacher and expect to complete assignments given in class as well as the remote learning assignments.

post_text:
Tomorrow begins the 2020 golf campaign for the Mustangs. Above all else, this is the first high school athletic event to take place in Morrison since February! This week has certainly tested us, but we will rise above. We will compete tomorrow for all those Spring athletes who lost their seasons and for all the Fall sports that were moved. This is a chance to get back to some sort of "normal." It's safe to say tomorrow is way more than just a "golf meet."

Players: this is a boys meet. Girls will have the day off. The bus leaves at 2:30. Please arrive early for your COVID screening. We will be hosting Rock Falls and Newman at Deer Valley. We tee off at 4p.m. Please have your MHS golf bags and team polos. You can wear any hat tomorrow, but have your nice dress pants/shorts on. The concession stand will be open. Spectators are allowed, but must sign-in. No spectator carts will be allowed to be rented. No water will be available on the course, so bring water or bring money.

post_text: WACC begins Thurs 8/20. Bus leaves at 7:25. Temp checks will be made prior to entering bus. Elevated temps will not be allowed to attend that day. WACC students will attend in person on all days WACC is in attendance. This includes days that MHS students are scheduled for remote learning. Students will join their MHS remote learning schedule upon returning from WACC. During 1:05 dismissals, student will be returning during 4th period. Students should contact their 4th period teacher & expect to engage in remote learning during the 1:05 dismissal timeframe. This is still subject to change based on MCUD6, WACC, &/or ISBE guidelines.

post_text: I have received a few questions about summer practices etc for our sports teams. As of 3:00 pm today Wednesday June 3rd the IHSA has not lifted its directive of no in person contact with athletes. Currently IHSA is working with the Illinois Department of Public Health to come up with guidelines for summer activities. Once those guidelines are released by the IHSA and reviewed by the district I will post them. Until they are released there should be no in person activities between coaches and athletes.

Just a reminder that the deadline for ordering the Northside and Southside 2019-2020 yearbook is this Friday (May 15)! Softcover books are $12.99 and an upgrade to a hardcover is $19.94. If you order ON or BEFORE Friday, May 15, shipping will be $2.99. Any orders placed AFTER Friday, May 15 will be charged $7.99 shipping. ALL yearbooks will be shipped directly to student homes in June! Thank you to everyone who has ordered so far!

Here is the link again to order.
https://www.treering.com/validate?PassCode=1013172392852488

post_text: Hello Families! If you have library books to return, there is now a spot at each school where you can return books on packet pick-up day. At the high school, there is a labeled table outside the library. Please place library books on the table. At the junior high, Southside, and Northside, there is a labeled box or tub in each packet pick-up area. Please place all library books in the box. Currently, there are over 700 books checked out in the district, and we would like to get as many of these back as possible. If you have books to return and cannot attend a packet pick-up before the end of the remote learning year, please contact Mrs. Stevenson at jennifer.stevenson@morrisonschools.org to make other arrangements for book return. Thank you!

post_text:
On Tuesday the IHSA officially cancelled the spring sports state series for Illinois High School and with Governor Pritzker's suspension of in person learning last Friday all Spring activities for MCUD #6 unfortunately are cancelled for this year.

Spring activity fees will be applied to next year's registration fees. However, if you wish to have your Spring activity fee refunded now please contact the District Office. The District will process and distribute refund checks as soon as possible to those requesting refunds.

Thank you for your continued patience during this unprecedented time.

Sincerely,
Scott Vance
Superintendent

post_text:
Dear Northside and Southside Families,

We know that these last few weeks have been full of changes, challenges and some stressful situations. Now that you’ve gotten through your first week of remote learning, Mr. Geiger and I would like to provide some strategies that can help deal with stress and promote positive thinking. Mindfulness is taught to children and adults to recognize how our bodies are feeling and clear our minds so that we can relax and think about the positive things around us. Try the video with your family. The more you practice, the better you will feel! Please contact Mr. Geiger or Mrs. Gettes, School Counselors, if you have questions or concerns.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=shR8DLyOkcg

post_text:
Please read the following message from the Northside/Southside PTO: Based on the district’s closing from March 16-30, 2020 due to COVID - 19, we have decided to cancel the Hurts Donut fundraiser this year. Although we’re disappointed that we had to make this choice, we are uncertain as to what the next few weeks will bring and if we could make the fundraiser up at a later date.

Students who have already turned in their fundraiser forms and money will have the envelopes returned to them when school reopens. If an earlier timeframe is desired, please private message our Facebook page or a member of the PTO.

As this fundraiser was meant to provide programming and cover the cost of field trip bussing for our Northside and Southside students, we hope to find other ways of raising funds in the near future.

National Online Safety has put together some fantastic resources for parents about social media apps, online games, and trending issues so they can have informed discussions with their children. THESE ARE PICTURES OF THE DOCUMENTS to give you an idea of what's available/discussed.

All resources, plus much more, can be accessed from the National Online Safety website: https://nationalonlinesafety.com/resources/wake-up-wednesday/
You can register for free and get a weekly update.

You can download some of the resources from a Google Drive folder: http://bit.ly/2v8rsEX (additional resources available from National Online Safety website, )

Visit the National Online Safety Facebook page: https://www.facebook.com/NationalOnlineSafety/
